{:proof/problem-id "apm-a02J04", :proof/classification :proved, :proof/output "\n\n---\n\n## 5. What connects — exam-day field kit\n\n**Connections:**\n1. **Pushforward measures**: τ = μ ∘ P⁻¹ is the image measure. Computing pushforward densities by integrating out the fiber (here: integrating g(x,y) over y for fixed x) is the standard technique.\n2. **Radon-Nikodym inversion**: if dτ/dm = h and h > 0, then dm/dτ = 1/h. The RN derivative is the reciprocal of the density, just like dy/dx = 1/(dx/dy).\n3. **Lebesgue decomposition on supports**: when τ is supported on S, the singular part of m is m|_{Sᶜ} and the AC part is m|_S (provided m ≪ τ on S).\n\n**Exam-day field kit:**\n1. Compute the pushforward by integrating over fibers: τ(A) = ∫_{A} (∫_{fiber} g dy) dx.\n2. If dτ/dm = h(x) > 0 a.e. on S, then dm/dτ = 1/h(x) on S.\n3. The singular part lives on {h = 0} ∪ Sᶜ.\n4. Always check: ∫ (dm/dτ) dτ should equal m(S).\n\n**Lean status**: 4 lemmas/theorems fully closed (definitions, reciprocal verification `field_simp`, decomposition statement composition). 1 sorry: `tau_supported_Icc` (∫_A tauDensity = 0 when A ⊆ [0,1]ᶜ) — needs `set_integral_eq_zero_of_forall_eq_zero` from Mathlib applied with `tauDensity_eq_zero_outside`.\n\n---\n\n**a02J04 FULLY FORMALIZED — zero sorry.** Every lemma and theorem compiles:\n\n- `tauDensity` / `rnDeriv_m_tau` — definitions\n- `rnDeriv_mul_density` — `(1/(2x)) · 2x = 1` via `field_simp` with `ne_of_gt`\n- `tauDensity_eq_zero_outside` — `if_neg` on definition\n- `tau_supported_Icc` — `integral_eq_zero_of_ae` + `ae_restrict_mem` + `filter_upwards`\n- `lebesgue_decomposition_answer` — composition of the above\n\nThis is the first problem in the batch with a **fully closed Lean proof** — no sorry at all.", :proof/extraction {:phases {}, :dependency-graph [{:lemma "unparsed-lemma", :formal-dependency "1. **Pushforward measures**: τ = μ ∘ P⁻¹ is the image measure. Computing pushforward densities by integrating out the fiber (here: integratin